This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of imitation learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model can be applied to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) to enhance learning in multiagent environments. Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of the proposed model with prioritized sweeping, which is a technique commonly used in Markov decision processes (cs.MA).
